The paper deals with controlling formations of mobile agents, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The use of internal model principle for robust output regulation control suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The use of gradient-based controllers and local estimators suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
